Confidence in the visual👇🏼

“Don’t get my face in it, or cover it with the hair….” 

We’ve all heard this from clients! But what if they had the opportunity to see what we see… put that camera on SELFIE MODE!

- confidence
- self love
- vibrance
- energy
- sex appeal

Seriously, I am an example of feeling uncomfortable when a pic is being taken, but when I can see what the camera sees, it’s easier to allow myself to feel the beauty that is inside myself and on the outside! We feel the best when we too have a visual!

Tell your client to just have fun with the camera and shoot a video so you can snag those still shots! Save this video and show your clients as a little example of how to amp up the content for their stylist!  Show them their video after and boost their egos! They are beautiful humans! Celebrate them!

Variation up close — Let’s break it down.

*creating subtle movement and seamless transition is key to an effective lived-in result using my latest placement mapping

— variation in panel weave - movement in size of weave will provide a unique and one of a kind result for every individual 

— teasing the base of your highlights to take advantage of the natural base and use it for target shade match for final root base 

— add in half pull-through depth drop slices between highlight panels - as seen in top left one 1/2 shade lighter than final root base to allow transition from one tone of depth to the next, darkest at the base 

— as seen in lower left pic, the depth is more visible rather than the pic on the top right which will result in a more subtle amount of depth to shine through all due to the size and depth of your highlight weave and tease

- bottom right is the final result of this placement and it’s impact of natural lived-in hair 

SWIPE FOR FINAL RESULT FEOM TWO ANGLES 👌🏼

R a w — E m o t i o n 

*Parenting is not for the weak. It is challenging. It is exhausting. It is maddening. It is absolutely one of the hardest tests we will endure in our existence. To know if they hear you. To know if you are making a difference. To know if they know they how loved they really are. To know if they are going to be ok when you let them go into this insane place we call our world. 

*To those struggling to find peace in parenting, I’m in your corner rooting for you. Even when I feel I’m failing, I know they’re going to be ok. Always my why, forever my babies. 

*And to those who are new moms, moms to be, and those desperately trying to start their families, I’m rooting for you too! All stages of parenting are hard. From the very start, we struggle and are full of raw emotion. I’m in your corner! 

XO,
JPark
